        transition: "Next",
        text: [
            "<p>At first glance, it isn’t easy to see what a negative exponent implies. How do you multiply a number a negative number of times?</p>",
            "<p>Enter the </p><div class='ye'>reciprocal</div><p>The reciprocal of a number is the number that becomes <span class='example'>1</span> when <i>multiplied to the original number!</i></p>",
            "<p>We know that all integers are rational numbers and can be written as:</p>",
            {
                Example: "Math",
                Content: '\\frac{number}{1}'
            },
            "<p>Knowing this, an easy way to think about the reciprocal is what you get when you flip the number <b>upside-down</b>.</p>",
            "<p><i>A negative exponent tells us how many times we have to <span class='re'>multiply the reciprocal of the base</span></i></p>",
            "<p>This means we have:</p>",
            {
                Example: "Math",
                Content: '2^{-5} = (\\frac{1}{2})^5'
            },
            "<p>Then, using the power of a quotient rule, we get:</p>",
            {
                Example: "Math",
                Content: '2^{-5} = (\\frac{1}{2})^5 = \\frac{1^5}{2^5} = 2^{-5} = \\frac{1}{32}'
